	<p>
	  <strong>
		  What do you do with my data?
		</strong>
		<br>
		For starters, we keep it safe and do not and will not ever sell it to
		anyone. More specifically,
		<ul>
		  <li>The comments you make will be visible to other dads</li>
		  <li>
			  If you email us at hello@thedaddyapp.com, our
				correspondance will be private
			</li>
			<li>
			  If you later on want to delete your account and have already made
				comments, suggested new features, replied to some other dads, etc,
				your name will be displayed as "Anonymous" and your account and personal
				data will be removed from our database
			</li>
		</ul>
	</p>

	<p>
	  <strong>
		  Can I delete my account?
		</strong>
		<br>
		We'd hate to see you go, but yes you can. As of now, email
		hello@thedaddyapp.com to let us know you want to be removed and we'll
		take care of the rest. It'll be like your personal data never existed on
		this site.
	</p>

	<p>
	  <strong>
		  Do you have any swag for sale?
		</strong>
		<br>
		Not yet, but soon! We have some thoughts on what to sell, but let us know
		what kind of swag you'd want either on the
		<%= link_to "Feedback", feedbacks_path %> page or directly
		through email at hello@thedaddyapp.com.
	</p>

	<p>
	  <strong>
		  How can I get involved and help The Daddy App?
		</strong>
		<br>
		It'd be great to have you onboard: let us know how you'd like to get
		involved with an email to hello@thedaddyapp.com and we'll take it from
		there.
	</p>

	<p>
	  <strong>
		  What's the "üö® Report" feature for?
		</strong>
		<br>
		If someone's comment goes against our
		<%= link_to "Community Guidelines", community_guidelines_path %>, hit this
		link to let us know it deserves some attention. Each report will be handled
		on a case-by-case basis. Thanks, in advance, for keeping this a "good vibes
		only" kind of space.
	</p>

	<p>
	  <strong>
		  Can I download this app on my phone?
		</strong>
		<br>
		Not yet!; there's nothing to download: The Daddy App is a web application
		and not a mobile application, which means you get to it by visiting
		"thedaddyapp.com" on your favorite browser like Safari, Chrome, Firefox,
		etc. One day we'll have an app you can download from the Apple Store
		or Google Play store to give you the most native experience you're used to
		from your other apps.

		<p>
		  Until then, you can add this site to your home screen for easy access.
			On Apple phones and tablets, tap the share button and then hit "Add to
			Home Screen". For Android users, the steps are similar but it depends on
			your phone.
		</p>
	</p>

	<p>
	  <strong>
		  I tapped the "üóì Question of the Day" link, but instead want to leave a
			general comment &mdash; how do I get rid of it?
		</strong>
		<br>
		No worries, just refresh the page next time and it'll reset by itself.
	</p>
